<section id="section_hb5_4sn_sjb">
<p id="p_ob5_4sn_sjb">Scriptorium, one of our partners in the US, has launched the LearningDITA website.</p>
<p id="p_lyr_3rn_sjb">It is a free and basic e-learning course for anyone who wants to learn DITA. You learn about the DITA specification and the different topic types in DITA, and also how to make bookmaps.</p>
<p id="p_lkv_krn_sjb">The course itself is written in DITA, making use of the <xref href="http://oxygenxml.com/doc/m/dita1.2_spec/archSpec-learningTraining.html" format="html" scope="external">DITA-specialization for e-learning</xref>.</p>
<p id="p_d31_lsn_sjb">More info on: <xref href="https://learningdita.com/about/" format="html" scope="external"/></p>
</section>
